00:26:41.000 --> 00:27:03.879
And it was also to do with the fact that when
they look through all the reviews that they

00:27:03.879 --> 00:27:23.720
could put on a cover, who could be a more
compelling visual image than they had this

00:27:23.720 --> 00:27:33.460
brilliant drawing of Superman, you know, flying
across the cover of the book review.

00:27:33.460 --> 00:27:46.350
So the timing was, turned out to be good for
lots of reasons.

00:27:46.350 --> 00:28:09.769
The other golden thing if you want to sell
a book, is there is one person, radio it turns

00:28:09.769 --> 00:28:14.909
out sells books better than any media.

00:28:14.909 --> 00:28:25.649
There is one person in radio, I don't know
if anybody is an NPR person, but Terry Gross

00:28:25.649 --> 00:28:29.050
